  <title>SET DESCENDING Command</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Commands</keyword>
    <keyword>Databases</keyword>
    <keyword>Index/order</keyword>
    <keyword>SET DESCENDING command</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SET DESCENDING Command</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="__CommandInclude" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Purpose</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Change the descending flag of the controlling order.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Syntax</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET DESCENDING ON | OFF | (<text styleclass="Italic">&lt;lToggle&gt;</text>)</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Bold"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Note: The initial default of this setting depends on whether the controlling order was created with descending as an attribute.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Description</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET DESCENDING is functionally equivalent to OrdDescend(). &#160;</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><snippet src="__IncludeLibRT" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">See Also</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Function_OrdDescend">OrdDescend()</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
